title: For Sale:   Chris Reeve large Sebenza 21
postcontent: Im the first owner of this great knife. Bought in Jan of 17. Sales receipt will verify it was purchased from authorized seller. Comes with original box, and everything that came with the box.This knife is used and shows signs of wear. There is some wear to the anodized finish on the thumbstud. There is cosmetic blemishes in the titanium scales. Im sure Chris Reeve can probably make it look like new if such things matter to you. To be honest, the knife did not come that sharp from the factory. I have used a Spyderco Sharpmaker on it, maybe twice or so, but have never been aggressive. It could still use a good sharpening but I don't feel like my skills are good enough to justify getting too crazy with sharpening on such a nice high dollar knife. I will leave that to the next owner to figure out. There are imperfections on the blade edge, either from actual use and/or sharpening. I think I used to cut feathersticks one time, and other than mostly just a few envelopes and boring household tasks, etc. Basically, carried "some" and actually used little. Ive NEVER done anything abusive to this knife. I dont baton with folding knives, use them as pry bars etc. Besides, this knife is too expensive to do things like that with. Blade is centered well and everything locks up nice and tight. It feels pretty smooth, and I would guess it will get smoother with age if what some people on the forums say is true. This is not the knife for the collector seeking perfection. It is the knife for the guy who wants to own a Large Sebenza 21 for less than $410, and doesn't mind cosmetic issues, or taking the time to get it shipped to Chris Reeve for spa treatment and or sharpening (if you don't sharpen knives yourself).I prefer face to face. I will not sell to anyone under 18. Proof of age required if I am in doubt, located in Waverly.Email for link to more pics.Thanks for looking-

title: For Sale:  Walther CCP (9mm) + Alien Gear 3.0 Holster
postcontent:
Great handgun, shot it several times at Gat Guns over the summer.   I bought it from a fellow gun-guy at work.   Still not broken in.  I put 100 rounds through it this summer.  I think it had a total of 200 rounds from previous owner.  This Walther CCP comes with an Alien Gear 3.0 Holster ($40 value) as well.  I recently purchased a muzzle loader for being able to hunt all 3 seasons now.  I have a carry gun and this one is just sitting on my shelf.   I have posted a description below of standard Walther description.  I qualified 30/30 for my carry license in May.  This is a great gun.  Just want to go smaller.
SOFTCOIL GAS TECHNOLOGY
The all new CCP (Concealed Carry Pistol) in 9mm Luger has an ideal combination of style, ergonomics, size, shape, accuracy, and ability to conceal comfortably. The new Walther SOFTCOIL™ gas-delayed blowback technology works to make the CCP an excellent concealed carry firearm.
The CCP’s SOFTCOIL™ gas-delayed blowback system uses gas pressure from the ignited cartridge by directing it through a small port in the barrel in front of the chamber to slow down and delay the rearward motion of the slide. This is accomplished by means of a piston contained inside of a cylinder located under the barrel that opposes the rearward motion of the slide until the gas pressure has declined after the bullet has left the barrel. This allows the slide to end its rearward motion, opening the breech, and ejecting the empty cartridge case.

postcontent: Up for sale or trade is an HK 45 Compact Tactical carry package.This handgun is a beast! This has long been one of my favorite pistols however I'm finding that I shoot 9mm far more due to the cost. I simply can't afford to utilize this pistol the way I would like at the range. I'm looking to sell it so I can pickup some of the other 9mm's I've been wanting.This gun comes with the following:HK 45C/CT with factory night sightsHK factory threaded barrelHK factory non-threaded barrelV3 decocker only leverV3 detent plate2, 10 round magazines2, 8 round flush fit magazine for carryDale Fricke "The Archangel" IWB Kydex holster FOR the HK 45CT extended barrelDale Fricke "The Archangel" IWB Kydex spare magazine carrierThen it also comes with the extra back straps, the case and everything else one would include.I wanted to explain the "V3 decocking lever and detent plate" that is included as some may not know. From the factory the HK 45CT comes as a V1 firearm which means it's a DA/SA pistol with a manual safety and decocking lever. The HK 45CT as issues to the US NAVY SEALS does not have a manual safety. The lever only decocks the hammer. I wanted to clone the US NAVY SEALS HK 45CT's so I bought the V3 lever and V3 detent plate. The gun comes with BOTH the V1 and V3 levers and detent plates so you an choose how you want to set it up.With everything I have for this HK, I have well over $1600.00 dollars into it. I'm not going to bother listing it all out, if your interested you can probably figure out what this is worth.I think I'm looking for another GLOCK 19 Gen4 possibly with Trijicon HD night sights?
